SEMDL Help Topic: reference merge

Usage:
- `ssd merge <input.ssd> --stdout`
- `ssd merge <input.ssd>`
- `ssd merge <input.ssd> --dry-run`
- `ssd merge <input.ssd> --out <output.ssd> [--dry-run]`
- `ssd merge <input.ssd> [--stdout|--dry-run|--out <output.ssd> [--dry-run]] --prefer-source inline|sidecar
- `ssd merge <input.ssd> [--stdout|--dry-run|--out <output.ssd> [--dry-run]] [--prefer-source inline|sidecar] --fail-on-conflict`

Status:
- `--stdout` returns the merged inline view of `.ssd` with an optional paired `.ssm`.
- Bare apply and `--dry-run` require a paired `.ssm`; in-place apply removes that sidecar after writing inline output.
- `--out <output.ssd>` writes merged inline output without modifying the source `.ssd` or paired `.ssm`.
- `--prefer-source inline|sidecar` changes which source wins for sidecar-owned duplicate field conflicts; without it, paired `.ssm` keeps precedence.
- `--fail-on-conflict` fails before output or mutation when inline source and paired sidecar disagree on the same sidecar-owned field.

Related help:
- `ssd help grammar`
- `ssd help samples`

Sample:
- `ssd merge docs/examples/minimal.ssd --stdout`
- `ssd merge docs/examples/minimal.ssd --out docs/examples/merged-output.ssd --dry-run`
- `ssd merge docs/examples/merge-conflict-source.ssd --stdout --prefer-source inline`
- `ssd merge docs/examples/merge-conflict-source.ssd --stdout --fail-on-conflict`
